By Martins Ifijeh The Lagos State Government has discharged 31 COVID-19 patients from its isolation centres, bringing to 1,025 the number of successfully treated persons in the state. Announcing this Sunday, the Incident Commander on COVID-19 in Lagos State, Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu said the discharged patients consist of 25 males and six females. He said: “Six were discharged from Onikan, four from Gbagada, two from Agidingbi, six from Lekki and 13 from Lagos University Teaching Hospital (LUTH) isolation centres. “With this, the number of COVID-19 confirmed cases that have been successfully managed and discharged in Lagos has risen to 1025.”